snippet.textDisplay:
I love this song except for one, unnecessary component... "Pal pal tu hi tu, dam dam tu hi tu". I mean it really drags the whole song down taking it from a mellow, jazzy, romantic song and turning it into a pop song that can't decide if it wants to be jazz, r&b or pop. 
When I'm laying on the sofa, reading and have the windows open with this song playing, the only thing that yanks me back from wherever this song takes me is that screaming of pal pal and dam dam. Am I making sense to anyone else? I feel like the whole mood and ambience of the song is just ruined by Shiraz Uppal trying to pretend he's a power vocalist
